## User Story

As a tester, I want to verify that the admin page form fields are present, show correct state, enforce length limits, and that the password change form rejects a wrong current password, so that `/zone/admin/` form coverage is automated safely.

## Context

`/zone/admin/` is currently untested beyond navigation/API. The form contains a password change section (3 fields), email, IP block, cookie blocking radio buttons (Tak/Nie), and SMS tracking fields. Submitting with the real current password would change it and break `auth.setup.ts` on every subsequent run. The server rejects a wrong current password immediately regardless of whether the new password fields match — so there is only one safe, testable password scenario.

Style selector is out of scope for this story. File to extend: `pages/authenticated/admin.page.ts`.

## Acceptance Criteria

**Given** I am on `/zone/admin/`
**Then** the email field has a non-empty value
**And** the cookie blocking radio "Nie" is checked
**And** all form fields (email, IP block, password ×3, SMS fields) are editable

**Given** I fill current password = `"test"` (intentionally wrong) and any values in new/confirm fields
**When** I click the password-change submit button
**Then** an error message is visible indicating the current password is incorrect

**Given** I inspect the `maxlength` attribute of each text field on the page
**When** I attempt to type more characters than `maxlength` allows
**Then** the field value is truncated to `maxlength` (front-side enforcement)

## Implementation Hint

```ts
// NEVER fill currentPasswordField with the real credential.
// The server rejects a wrong current password before checking new vs confirm,
// so new/confirm values are irrelevant to the outcome.
await adminPage.currentPasswordField.fill('test');
await adminPage.newPasswordField.fill('abc123');
await adminPage.confirmPasswordField.fill('abc123');
await adminPage.passwordSubmitButton.click();
await expect(adminPage.passwordError).toBeVisible();

// Max-length pattern:
const maxLen = await adminPage.emailField.getAttribute('maxlength');
await adminPage.emailField.fill('a'.repeat(Number(maxLen) + 10));
await expect(adminPage.emailField).toHaveValue('a'.repeat(Number(maxLen)));
// Do NOT submit after this fill.
```

## Definition of Done

- [ ] `AdminPage` getters added for all form fields, radio buttons, and the password-section submit button
- [ ] Test: email non-empty, cookie radio "Nie" is checked, all fields editable
- [ ] Test: wrong current password → error message visible
- [ ] Test: `maxlength` enforced on every text field (input truncated, form never submitted after fill)
- [ ] `tsc --noEmit` passes, `npm run format` applied
- [ ] All tests pass on Chromium, Firefox, WebKit, Mobile Chrome, Mobile Safari
